@ryanofsky Is that what they call copyrighting skills? Regardless I'll take it. Very informative and precise.

@paplorinc This was what made me still feel it was okay to use endianness terminology:

Quoting sipa https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/30526#issuecomment-2254159503:
> Its byte encoding can properly be described as little-endian.

He was more against applying endianness to to numbers, as it is a memory-order concept for bytes. But I agree avoiding the concept here because of the `uint32_t` involved is wise.

